    "body": "## Purpose\n\nPrepare the creative/product foundation that Codex will later implement for Stage 6 Step 9.\n\nThis PR is **documentation/data only** and intentionally does **not** modify runtime/game code. It captures the corrected product direction from the user and live Notion memory: five unmistakable generational UI personas (`Boomer / Gen X / Millennial / Zoomer / Alpha`) built from semantic-equivalence rows, with Russian-first copy and Step 9 intensity rules.\n\n## Current authority\n\nBaseline main: `7673f3487b0dd52c0c5cb2c7826f4e3fe5cc570e`.\n\nLive Notion authority before this branch: `MEMORY_REV 2026-07-23-1119-JST`.\n\nThe later Stage 6 Step 9 bold generational retro-audit supersedes earlier overly cautious/sterile tone guidance where that guidance would neutralize profile identity. The valid rule is `NO FALSE OR MISUSED SLANG`, not `NO SLANG`.\n\n## Important Gen X finding\n\nCurrent runtime already contains partial Gen X plumbing:\n- birth-year band `1965-1980 -> genX` exists;\n- canonical normalization `genx -> genX` exists;\n\nbut first-class support is incomplete:\n- `UI_PROFILE_REGISTRY.supported` omits `genX`;\n- text-mode resolver falls Gen X through to Millennial;\n- current start-screen/profile dictionaries omit Gen X;\n- current Stage 6 presentation `PROFILE_KEYS` omits Gen X;\n- current preview/smoke matrices assume four profiles.\n\nSo Gen X is not a new generation-band invention. It is an unfinished first-class profile.\n\n## Added artifacts\n\n1. `STAGE6_STEP9_FIVE_PROFILE_FOUNDATION.md`\n   - five-profile authority;\n   - Step 9 semantic-equivalence model;\n   - intensity ladder;\n   - profile character bibles;\n   - Gen X implementation gap;\n   - hidden-label acceptance;\n   - toast architecture preservation;\n   - Codex boundary.\n\n2. `STAGE6_STEP9_RU_SEMANTIC_MATRIX_DRAFT.md`\n   - human-review table;\n   - 48 high-frequency semantic intents;\n   - five Russian candidate renderings per intent;\n   - persistent UI, conflict, economy/toasts, outcomes, vote, empty states, cop flow, cooldown, onboarding, NPC/reaction archetypes.\n\n3. `stage6_step9_ru_semantic_matrix_draft.json`\n   - machine-readable companion for later deterministic implementation;\n   - status remains `DRAFT_FOR_USER_APPROVAL`.\n\n4. `STAGE6_STEP9_CODEX_IMPLEMENTATION_CONTRACT.md`\n   - exact no-creativity contract for Codex;\n   - Gen X first-class requirements;\n   - five-profile validations;\n   - unified-toast invariant;\n   - suggested implementation waves after copy freeze.\n\n## Important status\n\nNo copy row in this PR is implementation authority yet.\n\nAll semantic-matrix rows are `DRAFT_FOR_USER_APPROVAL`.\n\nCodex must not implement until User + ChatGPT explicitly freeze an approved matrix revision/hash.\n\nStage 6 remains **NOT COMPLETE**.\n\n## Exact diff\n\nExactly four new files, no runtime/game changes:\n- `STAGE6_STEP9_CODEX_IMPLEMENTATION_CONTRACT.md`\n- `STAGE6_STEP9_FIVE_PROFILE_FOUNDATION.md`\n- `STAGE6_STEP9_RU_SEMANTIC_MATRIX_DRAFT.md`\n- `stage6_step9_ru_semantic_matrix_draft.json`\n",
